task.summary: Default task
Seems to be able to upload stuff to the DB.
Started to work on the client-side TypeScript/HTML5 Canvas program that allows teachers to select regions of a PDF for questions. PDF rendering works.

Client-side question-selection with canvas rendering engine works. HiDPI screens are supported. Client-side JS creates a form for question properties, but (as yet) there is no way of submitting the questions' page regions.

Worked on improving the JS behind the form that gets the point values of each question when creating a test. It now has input validation, placeholder values, and disables submission if there is invalid input (also turns the box red). Still a JDBC error being thrown on the server, though (not fixed yet).
Client-side create_new_test_2 TypeScript now correctly sends JSON of the questions' data to the server-side Java, which correctly deserializes the JSON into Java objects.
Worked on why RenderTestController's renderer cache doesn't save across requests. It's emptying the HashMap each time, probably.

I've fixed the problem of RenderTestController not using cached PDFRenderer objects; the problem was that SparkJava runs the handlers for all requests in parallel, so the cached PDFRenderers weren't showing up until the handlers had already run. Now, the handlers signal if they are in the process of creating a PDFRenderer. If one handler is creating a PDFRenderer for a document, the other handlers requesting the same document will wait for it to appear in the cache.
Split create_new_test_2.ts into multiple files so that the CanvasRenderer and TestQuestion classes can be reused elsewhere.
Added a tsconfig.json so that the TypeScript checker would be able to see classes from other files.
Deleted some Eclipse-related and VSCode-related files that weren't necessary. Added package-lock.json to Git.

Moved all of the client-side TypeScript code for viewing rendered tests (PDF files) into a separate class (the TestViewer class in testviewer.ts). This allows the test viewer to be reused for multiple pages without repeating code.
Created the /test?test_id= page that lets users view tests that have already been created. Moved some global configuration of client-side PDF rendering code into global_parameters.ts.

Added the ability to designate one question per test as a "name" question where the student can write their name or other identification. The /create_new_test_2 page highlights this question in green and labels it "NAME".
Added support for the message_color session attribute, so that the software can set messages to be flashed on the next page to be a certain color (such as green/red to indicate success/failure).
Added a homepage (at the URLs "/" and "/index").
Added the /upload_student_answers page and corresponding database tables/controllers to upload scans of student answers to the database for later grading.

The /tests page now shows a list of uploaded student answer files with a button to upload more. Clicking on any of the already uploaded ones goes to /student_answer_file?student_answer_file_id=#, which sends back the raw PDF data for the user's browser to view.
Moved all controllers to their own package.
Started working on JavaDoc comments and other comments documenting the code. Main, CreateNewTest1Controller, and CreateNewTest2Controller are all fully documented.
Refactored all of the controllers to inherit their PersistentStorage and a constructor from controllers.Controller.

Worked on the /grade_test page for grading tests. It can use AJAX to show a list of available questions to grade, but it cannot actually display/grade questions yet. Added the /render_student_answer page that renders regions of student answer files into raw PNG data.

/grade_test page can now render and show individual student answers. BIG CHANGE: CanvasRectangle objects now use inches for coordinates (not pixels as before). They are converted to pixels only for rendering. CanvasImage objects continue to use pixels. This change required significant refactoring. Also added a retrieveStudentAnswers TypeScript function that uses a Promise.

/grade_test page now uses regular tags instead of a canvas. It now uses a table to show the side-by-side view for grading. "Grade Test" button on /tests now only appears when student answers have been uploaded.
Pressing ENTER after entering a student score now advances to the next student answer.

MILESTONE: Huge and complicated refactoring at every level so that test question objects now carry ID's with them, student answer generation happens only once (when the student answer file is initially uploaded), and student answers have their own unique ids.
MILESTONE: Scores entered on /grade_test are now actually saved to the database correctly in the student_answers table.
Bugfixed /grade_test's "show number of ungraded answers" functionality.
